  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Lifesaving Emergency Shelter and Non-Food Items Response to Displaced Internally Displaced Persons (IDPs) in Somali Region</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Through this project IOM is supporting households with life-saving humanitarian assistance through the provision of cluster approved in-kind emergency shelter and non-food item (ES/NFI) kits and cash-based assistance for NFI materials. Assistance provided aims at improving the living conditions of communities displaced as a result of drought or conflict; often after loss of shelter, household assets, and crops, settled temporarily in open grounds or collective centers with no shelter or simple structures using tree branches that provide only minimal protection, privacy, safety and comfort.</narrative>
  </description>
